From: torch_npu-infra <torch_npu-infra@example.com>
Date: Sat, 8 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix PyTorch 2.12+ HostBlockPool API compatibility

PyTorch 2.12+ changed HostBlockPool structure:
- Removed 'pool' member from BlockPool
- Removed 'unmapped' member
- Renamed 'blocks' to 'blocks_' (private member)
- Changed internal implementation to use ska::flat_hash_set

This patch fixes torch_npu to work with PyTorch 2.12+ by:
1. Renaming torch_npu's BlockPool to NPUBlockPool to avoid conflicts
2. Keeping torch_npu's own implementation with blocks/unmapped members
3. Updating all BlockPool references to NPUBlockPool

diff --git a/torch_npu/csrc/core/npu/CachingHostAllocator.cpp b/torch_npu/csrc/core/npu/CachingHostAllocator.cpp
index 738b91b..6e81230 100644
--- a/torch_npu/csrc/core/npu/CachingHostAllocator.cpp
+++ b/torch_npu/csrc/core/npu/CachingHostAllocator.cpp
@@ -885,7 +885,7 @@ private:
         pool.blocks.insert(block);
     }
 
-    void process_events() override
+    void process_events()
     {
         while (true) {
             // Avoid calling cudaEventDestroy while holding a mutex, so move

-- 2.43.0
